<section class="page-margin contained">
    <p>We learned in these conversations how drillers currently solve the problem of going off plan – sometimes intentionally – and also that large and small crews seemed to operate in significantly different ways when problems arise. Invigorated by these insights, we sought to talk to more crews of varying sizes and work in different soil types.</p>
    <p>We were connected with a handful of drillers and foremen from across the country. To keep track of their stories, we created a journey map, similar to a game board, for plotting important information that came up during our conversations. We printed icons on different colored stickets to represent key moments and then wrote in the details from beginning to end. This kept the conversation fluid and showed us where we may need to probe further in real time.</p>
</section>

