    <h2 id="wireframing">Wireframing the interface</h2>
    <p>Armed with the context of how drill crews perform their jobs and analyze problems, I began blocking out various screens in Adobe XD. Our client was already adopting Google’s Material Design language for many of it’s newer apps and websites, so I used the Google guidelines and patterns for a first pass through the key features we were working on.</p>
    <p>Our team had access to a rugged PC setup identical to what is mounted on a rig, and I was able to use the touch screen as a second monitor to display the wireframes and grayscale screens so that we could test font size, contrast, target area, and overall layout.</p>
    <p>This became a valuable focal point within our team space for facilitating conversations with developers and our stakeholders during sprint demos around expected behavior.</p>
</section>

